First time trying Blue Collar was today and I have mixed feelings. I ordered the regular cheeseburger and although the taste was actually good, I felt like I was eating a mcdonalds burger. I mean a mcdonalds burger 10x better and with real ingredients, but it just had that mcdonalds "feel"... I'm not sure how to describe it. it even looks like a mcdonalds burger (see pic attached) and it was presented as such as well. Anyways the taste was good. The burger had no special sauce or anything particular about it, it was just a plain regular cheeseburger. The size was kind of small but they compensate with a huge bag of fries (they actually charge a lot for said fries). The price of the burger is directly proportional to the size of the burger, so there's that. But back to the fries, they ALSO tasted like mcdonalds fries.  The only bad experience I had tonight was that I ordered the food through Seamless, and it was a complete waste of our time. Placed the order at 9:00 and by 9:50 we were getting in our car to pick up our order after we received the 4th "delayed" text saying that the order will be ready between 10:30-10:40. This isn't the restaurants fault, but I had to bring it up either way. Blue Collar should choose another delivery company that actually delivers the orders to people within a reasonable time frame; not 1 hour and 40 minutes after you have placed an order. Now when we arrived to pick up the order, the guy said that they remade the burgers for us which is great. Gold star for that. The fries were cold and hard, but they remade the burgers and we appreciate it.  To conclude, would I recommend this place? Yes but with a disclaimer that includes: eat there or pick it up, don't expect huge-over-the-top burgers, expect a squished flat somewhat soggy burger, and just think of it as a 10x better mcdonalds burger.

This tucked away hip burger joint doesn't really match up with the neighborhood vibe of standard New York drab. It has bright  retro décor, a reasonable number of less then 4 seating (about 30 total), and medium volume themed music that makes chatting not a chore.  The menu is simple offering a few varieties of burgers, shakes, and fries. The large serving of chili cheese fries is suitably humongous and is fine for 4 people to share. The burgers aren't gigantic (comparable to Five Guys) but I would definitely go for the double; they do a fine representation of a soft bun American burger that isn't going to blow your mind but is still very satisfying. It was juicy and that meat patties weren't masked by over the top cheeses or sauces (though I think they have one... or it might have just been mayonnaise).  You order at the counter and they bring out a tray with your stuff. Took about 10 minutes to cook-up. Soda machine within easy reach.
